{"title_page": "Bhatni Bazar", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = \u092a\u093e\u0902\u0921\u0947\u092f \u091a\u094c\u0930\u093e\u0939\u093e\n| native_name_lang                = bhatni\n| other_name                      = Pandey chauraha\n| nickname                        = Pandey brother's\n| settlement_type                 = Pandey chauraha   Bhatni\n| image_skyline                   = 100\n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Uttar Pradesh\n| pushpin_label_position          = Right\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = 274701\n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Uttar Pradesh, India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|26.22|N|83.57|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = India\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1               = Utter Pradesh\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Deoria district|Deoria]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date                = \n| founder                         = \n| named_for                       = \n| government_type                 = \n| governing_body                  = \n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_rank                       = \n| area_total_km2                  = 10\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = 1000\n| population_total                = 1000\n| population_as_of                = 1200\n| population_rank                 = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_demonym              = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| demographics_type1              = Languages\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = [[Hindi language|Hindi,English Bhojpuri]]\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = 274701\n| postal_code                     = 274701\n| registration_plate              = wwwpandeychauraha@.\n| website                         = {{URL|pandeychauraha@.com}}\n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = Pandey chauraha\n}}\n'''Bhatni 'near by '' is a Pandey chauraha and a [[gram panchayat|behrs daber]] in the [[Deoria district]] in the Indian state of [[Uttar Pradesh]]. It is the capital of the Development block with the same name.\n\n==Geography==\nPandey chauraha is located at an average elevation of 4 km  above [[sea level]]. Bhatni is divided into two markets; one is known as [[Pandey brothers|Pandey chauraha bhatni bhatpar road]] (some suggest it was constructed by Pandey brother), and the other is the larger Pandey chauraha near bhatni Bazar. A sugar mill and a major railway connection Bhatni Junction ......\n\nNearby settlements include small towns such as Jigina Mishra, tenaya, BEHARADABER,  and Pandey chauraha in the North, Panditpura.Gownariya and hriom chauraha in the east,  Uska, Nonapar, Bharhe, Chaura and Sawrezi in the East ......\n\n==Demographics==\n<!-- Please do not post Personal message or Content, that violates rules of Wikipedia -->\n2000 [[Census of India|census]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040616075334/http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archivedate=2004-06-16|title= Census of India 2001: Data from the 2001 Census, including cities, villages and towns  (Provisional)|accessdate=2008-11-01|publisher= Census Commission of India}}</ref> pandey chauraha had a population of 1,381. Males constituted 42% of the population and females 48%. The town had an average literacy rate of 52%, higher than the national average of 59.5%; with a male literacy rate of 76% and a female literacy rate of 52%. 16% of the population is under 6.\n\n==Language==\nThe people of Bhatni speak [[Bhojpuri]] and [[Hindi]], although English is increasingly used by younger people of the area.\n\n==Education==\nTwo private colleges offer degrees: \u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u0938\u093f\u0926\u094d\u0927\u0947\u0936\u094d\u0935\u0930 \u0936\u0940\u0924\u0932\u0926\u0947\u0935 \u0928\u093e\u0930\u093e\u092f\u0923 \u092e\u0939\u093e\u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0932\u092f and \u0936\u094d\u0930\u0940 \u092c\u091a\u094d\u091a\u0928 \u0921\u0949\u0915\u094d\u091f\u0930 \u092d\u0940\u092e\u0930\u093e\u0935 \u0905\u0902\u092c\u0947\u0921\u0915\u0930 \u0907\u0902\u091f\u0930 \u0915\u0949\u0932\u0947\u091c (affiliated to D.D.U. Gorakhpur University). Subhash Intermediate College is in the heart of the city. It is one of the oldest colleges in a radius of 1.5 km. A government Junior High School is located in ..behara daber and bharhe chaura...\nThanks\n\n==Politics==\nBoth Behradaber and gram Panchayat have often been in the limelight for the politics . Pandey chauraha has seen much development since it was awarded the same status as Gram Panchayat behradaber..1 jaiprkash pandey 2.Hari prkash Pandey 3.Nanlal pandey 4.Subhash Chandra Pandey. By open Pandey chauraha 2000..... \n\nOnly B.J.P.... \u092d\u093e\u0930\u0924\u0940\u092f \u091c\u0928\u0924\u093e \u092a\u093e\u0930\u094d\u091f\u0940  \n\n==References==\n1.Census of india 2000; including cities ,villages and Pandey chauraha....(provisional ) {{Deoria district}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Deoria district]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Bhatni Bazar\n| native_name                     = \u092a\u093e\u0902\u0921\u0947\u092f \u091a\u09