{"title_page": "Enrico Echiverri", "text_new": "{{short description|Filipino lawyer and a politician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{BLP sources|date=August 2010}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name       = Atty. Enrico \"RECOM\" Echiverri\n| image      = ID Enrico\n| imagesize  = 51 KB\n| smallimage =\n| caption    = Photo of Ex-Mayor Echiverri\n| office      =  Member of the [[House of Representatives of the Philippines]] from the 1st District of the [[Caloocan]]\n| term_start     = June 30, 2013\n| term_end     = June 30, 2016\n| predecessor    = [[Oscar Malapitan]]\n| successor = Dale Malapitan\n| term_start2     = June 30, 1998\n| term_end2     = June 30, 2004\n| predecessor2    = [[Bobby Guanzon]]\n| successor2 = [[Oscar Malapitan]]\n| office3      =  [[Mayor of Caloocan]]\n| term_start3     = June 30, 2004\n| term_end3     = June 30, 2013\n| predecessor3    = [[Rey Malonzo]]\n| successor3 = [[Oscar Malapitan]]\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1954|11|18}}\n| birth_place    = [[Manila, Philippines]]\n| death_date     =\n| death_place    =\n| nationality    = [[Filipino people|Filipino]]\n| spouse         = Purificacion Malabanan Echiverri \n| relations      =\n| children       = RJ Malabanan Echiverri, Erich Barretto Echiverri\n| residence      = Caloocan\n| domicile       = Morning Breeze, Caloocan City\n| alma_mater   = [[De La Salle Araneta University]] <br /> [[San Beda University]] <br >[[Ateneo de Manila University]]\n| occupation     = Public Servant\n| profession     = Lawyer\n| religion       = [[Catholic Church in the Philippines|Roman Catholicism]]\n| signature      =\n}}\n\n'''Enrico Echiverri''' is a Filipino lawyer and a politician. He is a member of the [[Philippine House of Representatives]] representing the First District of [[Caloocan City]]. He is more fondly known as '''Recom'''.\n\n==Education==\nEchiverri spent his grade school years at Morning Breeze Elementary School. He finished his secondary studies at the [[De La Salle Araneta University|Gregorio Araneta University Foundation High School]] in [[Malabon]] in 1971. He took up AB Economics at [[San Beda University]]. Upon graduation, he studied at the [[Ateneo de Manila University]] and finished his degree in [[Bachelor of Laws]] in 1981.\n\n==Career==\nBefore he entered politics, Echiverri served as an arbiter and conciliator at the [[Department of Labor and Employment]] from 1981 to 1988 and simultaneously as legal counsel for [[Antonio Leviste|J. Antonio Leviste Company]] from 1984 to 1988. He was also appointed Director of the [[Movie and Television Review and Classification Board|Videogram Regulatory Board]] in the early 1990s.\n\nEchiverri's political career began when he was elected city councilor in [[Caloocan]] from 1988 to 1992. In 1995, he worked as Secretary to the Mayor under the city mayorship of actor-turned-politician [[Rey Malonzo]] until he ran for congress in 1998. He became the representative of the first district of Caloocan in the House of Representatives from 1998 to 2004. During his congressional stint, he was among the 'Spice Boys' who were instrumental in the [[Second EDSA Revolution|ousting]] of former [[List of Presidents of the Philippines|Philippine President]] [[Joseph Estrada]]. He was also a law professor in four universities, namely [[Miriam College|Maryknoll College]], [[San Beda College]], [[Far Eastern University]], and [[Manila Central University]].\n\nEchiverri was elected mayor in 2004 defeating Gigi Malonzo, Egay Erice, Macario \"Boy\" Asistio, Jr., and Luis \"Baby\" Asistio. He had been mayor for three terms from 2004-2013. During the 2013 elections, his son Ricojudge ran for mayoralty but lost to then representative for the city's north district [[Oscar Malapitan]].\n\nEchiverri ran for Mayor in the  [[2016 Philippine general election|2016]], but lost to incumbent mayor Oscar Malapitan.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/784987/incumbent-caloocan-mayor-beats-iglesia-backed-foe | title=Malapitan wins reelection | newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer|Inquirer]] | date=May 11, 2016 | accessdate=October 24, 2019 | first=Jodee A. |last=Agoncillo}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n* Dangal ng Bayan Award for Public Service, 12th Annual Asia-Pacific Excellence Award \n* Huwarang Ama for Public Service / Outstanding Father of the Year, National Mother's Day & Father's Day Awards \n* Innovative Solutions to Dumps and Waste Award (\u201cOut of the Box Award\u201d), Mother Earth Foundation\n* Bagong Bayani ng Caloocan Award, Humanitarian Mission \n* Recognition Award for the successful & effective implementation of DILG-NCR Programs, [[Department of the Interior and Local Government]] \n* Plaque of Merit, 2nd Best City Police Station of the Year, Philippine National Police \n* Distinguished Public Service Award - Exemplary Performance as a Leader, [[Integrated Bar of the Philippines]] \n* Hall of Fame Awardee, Most Outstanding Congressman, Congress Magazine, Makati Graduate School & Metropolitan Disseminators of Information Association (MEDIA) \n* [[Ramon Mitra, Jr.|Hon. Ramon V. Mitra]] [[San Beda College|Bedan]] Award for Legislation \n* \"Huwarang Filipino Awardee for Government & Public Service,\" Gintong Anak/Ina Awards, Parangal ng Bayan Foundation \n* \"Outstanding Legislator of the Year, Public Servant of the New Millennium,\u201d  Phil. Media Research and Progress Report Inc. \n* 2003 Year-Ender Excellence Award, National Consumers Affairs Foundation \n* [[Paul P. Harris|Paul Harris Fellow]], [[Rotary International]] \n* Most Outstanding City Councilor, [[League of Barangays of the Philippines|Association of Barangay Council]], 1992 \n* Most Outstanding Alumnus, [[De La Salle Araneta University|Araneta University Foundation High School]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n<!--- After listing your sources please cite them using inline citations and place them after the information they cite. Please see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. --->\n*[https://www.facebook.com/Mayor.Echiverri/] http://www.congress.gov.ph/members/search.php?id=echiverri-e&pg=coauth\n*[http://www.philstar.com/metro/574418/incumbents-still-win-caloocan] [http://ncr.dilg.gov.ph/home/index.php/news/177-dilg-recognizes-exemplary-local-government-units-of-the-national-capital-region http://ncr.dilg.gov.ph/home/index.php/news/177-dilg-recognizes-exemplary-local-government-units-of-the-national-capital-regio][http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/08/27/08/marjorie-barretto-%E2%80%98-time-finally-speak-up%E2%80%99][http://www.congress.gov.ph/members/search.php?id=echiverri-e&pg=auth]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Echiverri, Enrico}}\n[[Category:Members of the House of Representatives of the Philippines from Caloocan]]\n[[Category:Mayors of places in Metro Manila]]\n[[Category:Metro Manila city and municipal councilors]]\n[[Category:People from Caloocan]]\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:San Beda University alumni]]\n[[Category:Ateneo de Manila University alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Filipino lawyer and a politician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{BLP sources|date=August 2010}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name       = Atty. Enrico \"RECOM\" Echiverri\n| image      = \n| imagesize  = \n| smallimage =\n| caption    =\n| office      =  Member of the [[House of Representatives of the Philippines]] from the 1st District of the [[Caloocan]]\n| term_start     = June 30, 2013\n| term_end     = June 30, 2016\n| predecessor    = [[Oscar Malapitan]]\n| successor = Dale Malapitan\n| term_start2     = June 30, 1998\n| term_end2     = June 30, 2004\n| predecessor2    = [[Bobby Guanzon]]\n| successor2 = [[Oscar Malapitan]]\n| office3      =  [[Mayor of Caloocan]]\n| term_start3     = June 30, 2004\n| term_end3     = June 30, 2013\n| predecessor3    = [[Rey Malonzo]]\n| successor3 = [[Oscar Malapitan]]\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1954|11|18}}\n| birth_place    = [[Manila, Philippines]]\n| death_da